title: 12 Chess Books - October 2015 (gnv64)
description:
A collection of 12 chess books, 11 PDFs & 1 ePUB:

01. Grandmaster Repertoire 7: The Caro-Kann by Lars Schandorff
02. How Good Is Your Chess by Daniel King
03. How to Be Lucky in Chess by David LeMoir
04. How to Beat Your Dad at Chess by Murray Chandler
05. How to Become a Deadly Chess Tactician by David LeMoir
06. Kasparov's Fighting Chess 1993-1998 by Tibor Karolyi and Nick Aplin
07. Practical Rook Endings by Edmar Mednis
08. Sacrifices in the Sicilian by David Levy
09. The Complete Pirc by John Nunn
10. The Right Way to Play Chess by David Pritchard (epub)
11. How to Play the English Opening in Chess by Anatoly Karpov
12. The Bishop's Opening Explained by Gary Lane
